---
import SpecLineItem from "../SpecLineItem.astro";

interface Props {
  isIsolated?: boolean;
  isolatedComponentId?: string;
}
const { isIsolated = false } = Astro.props;
---

<SpecLineItem 
  title="02. // Typography"
  url={isIsolated ? "/resources/design-system" : "/resources/design-system/typography"}
  tags={[isIsolated ? "View All" : "Isolate"]}
  headingLevel="h2"
/>

<p>The Avionics typography system uses two carefully selected typefaces to create a technical, authoritative feel.</p>

<h3>Font Families</h3>
<pre><code>--f-sans: "Archivo", sans-serif;  /* Variable font with industrial character */
--f-mono: "B612 Mono", monospace; /* Aviation-grade monospace */</code></pre>

<p><strong>Archivo</strong> is a variable font designed for industrial and technical applications. <strong>B612 Mono</strong> was designed by Airbus for cockpit displays.</p>

<h3>Heading Styles</h3>
<p>All headings use uppercase transformation and expanded width for maximum impact:</p>

<pre><code>h1, h2, h3 {`{`}
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  font-variation-settings: "wdth" 110; /* Expanded width */
{`}`}</code></pre>

<table class="breakout">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Element</th>
      <th>Size</th>
      <th>Usage</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><code>h1</code></td>
      <td>2.5rem (40px)</td>
      <td>Page titles, main headings (one per page)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>h2</code></td>
      <td>1.5rem (24px)</td>
      <td>Major sections, chapter headings</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code>h3</code></td>
      <td>1.125rem (18px)</td>
      <td>Subsections, technical labels (uses monospace)</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
